rSDK/documentation/ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Allows to select the balance between result accuracy (precision) and missed barcodes (recall) for linear barcodes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some barcode types are naturally prone to false positives (e.g. MSI Plessey)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For those barcode types false positives can be drastically reduced (precision can be increased) by requiring that multiple scan-lines in the input scan to the same result."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, this stronger condition can lead to missed barcodes (lower recall)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Confirmation is avoided for barcode types, which are by design resistant to false positives, (e.g. Code128) to maximize recall."}],"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotbarcodescannersdk\/sbsdkonedconfirmationmode","title":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","kind":"identifier"}]}},"variantOverrides":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"\/references\/doc:~1~1net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK~1documentation~1ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK~1SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode2Of5Configuration\/title","value":"SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode2Of5Configuration"},{"op":"replace","path":"\/references\/doc:~1~1net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK~1documentation~1ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK~1SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode2Of5Configuration\/fragments","value":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode2Of5Configuration"}]},{"op":"replace","path":"\/references\/doc:~1~1net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScanner